Accuracy: Measures how factually correct the model's output is compared to the expected answer.
Completeness: Assesses whether the response fully addresses all parts of the query.
Hallucination: Detects when the model generates information not supported by the input or facts.
Context Relevance: Evaluates how well the response aligns with the context of the prompt.
Semantic Relevance: Checks if the meaning of the response logically matches the user's intent.
Consistency: Ensures the model provides stable and coherent answers across similar inputs.
